file: crates/ctx-context/tests/chain_serve.rs
behavior: Integration tests for `ctx_context::serve`, `hook`, and `session` against an in-memory `FakeEnv`, asserting chain ordering, directory/root target handling, absent-node markers, rendered output format, hook injection/dedup by session, and fail-open behavior on corrupt session state.
edit_notes:
  - Defines FakeEnv, a flat path->bytes map implementing the ctx_context::env::Env trait; is_dir is inferred from key prefixes ("<path>/"), not from an explicit directory marker.
  - FakeEnv::seeded() fixture layout (paths and contents) is relied on by nearly every test; changing it requires updating expected id/body assertions throughout this file.
  - Chain node ids and expected ordering (root rollup/intent, then per-directory-level rollup/intent, then leaf .ctx) encode the traversal contract of serve::chain_for; must stay in sync with that function's actual algorithm.
  - Absent-node body text is asserted verbatim ("(absent: no intent at this level)", body containing "no leaf") and must match serve.rs's literal marker strings.
  - render() output format asserted verbatim: "=== <id> [<kind>] ===\n<body>\n"; must match serve::render's formatting.
  - Session dedup test depends on hook::run consulting and updating per-session state (via session module) keyed by session_id from the event JSON.
  - corrupt_session_state_reads_as_empty writes directly to the .context/.cache/hook-<id>.json path that session::load reads; format/path must match session module's internal convention.
functions:
invariants:
  - serve::chain_for rejects any path escaping the repo root (absolute paths, "..", or "//" segments) with CtxError::PathEscape.
  - hook::run returns an empty string for events outside the repo, targeting .context/.git paths, or that are unparseable/pathless.
  - hook::run never errors on corrupt session state; treats it as an empty session (fail-open, may re-inject).
external_deps:
  - ctx_context::env::Env: trait FakeEnv implements to substitute a real filesystem in tests.